<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7712237>
    dc:description "FIG. 8.—Holotype of Pseudopaludicola ibisoroca sp. nov. (UFMT 16208, male, SVL ¼ 12.3 mm): (A) dorsal and (B) ventral view; (C) ventral view of hand; and, (D) ventral view of foot. Scale bar in panels C and D ¼ 1 mm. A color version of this figure is available on-line." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7712237/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7712239>
    dc:description "FIG. 9.—Live specimens of Pseudopaludicola ibisoroca sp. nov. from the municipality of Alto Taquari, Mato Grosso, Brazil: (A) adult male (UFMT 16142);" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7712239/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7712233>
    dc:description "FIG. 6.—Map of the portions of South America (inset) showing the geographic distribution of Pseudopaludicola motorzinho sp. nov. (circles), P. ibisoroca sp. nov. (triangle), P. ceratophŋes (diamonds), and P. boliƲiana (squares). Stars represent type localities. Closed symbols are records from the present work, and open symbols are records from the literature (Lynch 1989; De la Riva et al. 2000; Duré et al. 2004; Reichle 2006; Cole et al. 2013)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7712233/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7712241>
    dc:description "FIG. 10.—(A) Oscillogram of three short advertisement call series of Pseudopaludicola ibisoroca sp. nov. (16, 11, and 9 notes with concatenated pulses, respectively); (B) oscillogram and (C) spectrogram of 3 notes with concatenated pulses. Voucher call LH 40A–03, from specimen UFMT 16208, recorded at 0945 h on 13 October 2007 (air temperature ¼ 23.5°C) at Granada Farm (Alto Taquari, Mato Grosso, Brazil). A color version of this figure is available online." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7712241/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7712243>
    dc:description "FIG. 11.—Karyotpes of two specimens of Pseudopaludicola ibisoroca sp. nov. stained with Giemsa (A; ZUEC 13992), submitted to the Ag-NOR technique (B; ZUEC 13987) and C-banded (C; ZUEC 13992). Scale bar ¼ 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7712243/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

